    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA361-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu vāyilkaḷoṭu tōḻi uṟaḻntu colliyatu (ET: kūṟiyatu).</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said, being close with the mediators.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA361">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>           ciṟuvī mullaip peritukama ḻalari</l>
<l>           tāṉuñ cūṭiṉa ṉiḷaiyaru malaintaṉar</l>
<l>           vicumpukaṭap paṉṉa polampaṭaik kalimāp</l>
<l>           paṭumaḻai poḻinta taṇṇaṟum puṟavi</l>
<l>           ṉeṭunā voṇmaṇi pāṭuciṟan ticaippa</l>
<l>           mālai māṉṟa maṇaṉmali viyaṉakart</l>
<l>           tantaṉa neṭuntakai tērē yeṉṟu</l>
<l>           marumpaṭa rakala nīkki</l>
<l>           viruntayar viruppiṉa ṭiruntiḻai yōḷē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Very fragrant blossoms of small-blossomed jasmine</l>
<l>he himself wore, and [his] young [attendants] put [them] on, too.</l>
<l>The spirited horses with golden harness,</l>
<l>	as if passing over the sky,</l>
<l>have brought the long, befitting chariot</l>
<l>	to the wide mansion filled with sand that is gloomy in the evening,</l>
<l>	while the singing of the long-tongued clear bells sounded excellently</l>
<l>	through the cool fragrant woodland on which the passing rain had flown.</l>
<l>	Setting aside [for it] to depart the difficult affliction all the time</l>
<l>she with perfect jewels longed to engage in [preparing] a feast.</l>
      </lg>
      </div>
